{"lemma":"لَزَّ","slug":"لَزَّ","root":"ل.ز.ز","root_slug":"ل-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ز-ز","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"لَزَزْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"لَزَزْتِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"لَزَزْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"لَزَزْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"لَزَزْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"لَزَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"لَزَّت","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"لَزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"لَزَّتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"لَزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"لَزَزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَلُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَلْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَلُزِّي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَلُزِّينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَلُزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَلُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَلُزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَلُزُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَلْزُزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَلُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَلْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَلُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَلْزُز","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَلُزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَلُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَلُزّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَلُزّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَلُزُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَلُزُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَلْزُزْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَلُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَلُزّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"لَزَزْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"لَزَزْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43281"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43281","headword_ar":"لَزٌّ","root":"lz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zurofiynN","text_ar":"زُرْفِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.) In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walazazN qayonN","text_ar":"وَلَزَزٌ قَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAll~az~u Alz~urofiynu","text_ar":"وَاللَّزُّ الزُّرْفِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%84%D8%B2/","headword_ar":"لز","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=93996#6d6f18","body_html":"<h3>لز</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> لَزَّ الشَّىْءُ بِالشَّىْءِ, (<abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>,) [<abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr>, <abbr title=\"apparently\">app.</abbr> لَزِّ,] or لَزَّهُ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (so in a copy of the <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَزٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) The thing clave to the thing: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>:) it stuck, or adhered, to it. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) See also 8. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [Hence,] لَزَزْتَ بِى يَا فُلَانُ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) [Thou hast importuned me, or wearied me by thine importunity, O such a one]. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> لَزَّهُ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَزٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and لَزَزٌ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, and so in a copy of the <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) or لَزَازٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, and so in a copy of the <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) He fastened it, or made it fast; or he bound it, or tied it; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> شَدَّهُ: and he stuck it, or made it to adhere; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) as also ↓ الزّهُ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> إِلْزَازٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) [But it is afterwards said in the <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>, that, <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to the <abbr title=\"The Takmilah fī l-Ṣiḥāḥ of al-Saghānī\">TS</abbr>, أَلْزَزْتُ بِهِ in the sense of أَلْصَقْتُ بِهِ was disallowed by <abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>.]) You say also, لَزَّهُ بِهِ, (<abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَزٌّ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) He made it to cleave to it; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>;) like the لِزَاز of a house or chamber. (<abbr title=\"El-Leyth Ibn-Nasr Ibn-Seiyar, held by El-Azberee to be the author of the “Eyn,” which he calls “Kitab Leyth” (al-Layth b. Muẓahffar al-Kināni)\">Lth</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) and لُزَّا They (two camels) were tied together: and they (the two shanks of a camel) were straitly connected in the shackles. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> He fastened it, namely a door, with a لِزَاز, or bar; he barred it. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> He thrust or pierced him [with a spear or the like]. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Turkish translation of al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">TK</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> لَزَّهُ إِلَى كَذَا (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) He necessitated him, or constrained him, to have recourse to, or to do, such a thing. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 2 لَزَّزَهُ He (God) caused him to be compact and strong in make. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) 3 لَا زَزْتُهُ, (<abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لِزَازٌ, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) I associated with him; became his companion. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 4 الزّهُ: see 1.<span class=\"sense\">8</span> التزّ بِهِ It became coupled with it, and stuck to it. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) See also 1.<br><br>رَجُلٌ كَزٌّ لَزٌّ A niggardly, tenacious, man: (<abbr title=\"al-Azharī, author of the Tahdhīb\">Az</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or the latter <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr> is an <abbr title=\"إِتْبَاعٌ\">imitative sequent</abbr>. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> لَزُّ شَرٍّ: see لِزَازُ شَرٍّ.<br><br>لِزٌّ شَرٍّ: see لِزَازُ شَرٍّ.<br><br>لَزَزٌ: see لِزَازٌ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> Straitness, difficulty, distress; or the like; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> شِدَّةٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> A state of crowding together of people in a narrow compass. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> عَيْشٌ لَزَزٌ A strait, or difficult, life (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) لِزَازٌ A piece of wood with which a door is fastened; the bar of a door; (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) as also ↓ لَزَزٌ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) [Said in the <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, where it is not explained, to be from لِزَازُ خَصْمٍ, <abbr title=\"quod vide (i.e. on this [matter], go see...)\">q. v.</abbr> infra.; but <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to the <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, it is proper, not <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>.]<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> هُوَ لِزَازُ مَالٍ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) He is one who [by close and constant attention] takes good care of camels, or other property. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) [Hence,] جَعَلْتُكَ لِزَازًا لِفُلَانٍ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) I have made or appointed thee [to be a manager of such a one;] not to suffer such a one to disobey or oppose. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> هُوَ لِزَازُ خَصْمٍ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) [He is one who cleaves to an adversary in contention or litigation]. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, A.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> إِنَّهُ لِزَازُ خُصُومَةٍ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Verily he is pertinacious in contention or litigation; commissioned and able to manage it. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> فُلَانٌ لِزَازُ شَرٍّ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) and شَرٍّ ↓ لَزِيزُ, and شَرٍّ ↓ لِزُّ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and لَزُّ شَرٍّ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Such a one is one who pertinaciously adheres to evil or mischief. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) لَزُوزٌ an <abbr title=\"إِتْبَاعٌ\">imitative sequent</abbr> to عَجُوزٌ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) لَزِيزُ شَرٍّ: see لِزَازٌ.<br><br>مِلَزٌّ, applied to a man, and in like manner, without ة, to a woman, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Vehement, or pertinacious, in adhering. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Vehement in contention or litigation; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) pertinacious in adhering to that which he desires, or seeks, to obtain. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) مُلَزَّزٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or مُلَزَّزُ الخَلْقِ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) A man (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) compact and strong in make; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) having a well-knit frame. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.)"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=93996#17b8f0","body_html":"<h3>لز</h3><span class=\"sense\">3</span> لَازَّهُ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> ضَايَقَهُ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>, <abbr title=\"under the heading\">voce</abbr> ذَاقَنَهُ.) لَزٌّ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> زُرْفِينٌ. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) In the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr>, وَلَزَزٌ قَيْنٌ is a mistake for وَاللَّزُّ الزُّرْفِينُ."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=93996#9879d9","body_html":"<div>لز</div><div>اللَز: لُزُوْمُ الشيْءِ بالشَّيْءِ؛ كَلِزَازِ البابِ. ورَجُل مِلَزُّ في خُصُوْمَتِهِ. وهو لِزَاز ُخَصْمٍ. ويزَازُ مالٍ: أي حَسَنُ القِيَام عَليه. والمِلَزُ: السًرِيْعُ الشدِيدُ الذيَ يَلُزُّ الدَّوَابَّ عِنْدَ الرَّكْضِ أي يزينها وقيل: هو الشدِيدُ العَضَلِ والخَلْقِ. لأنه لَكَزٌ لَزٌّ: تَاْكِيْدٌ. ومُلَزَزُ الخَلْقِ: مُجْتَمِعٌ. واللز: الطَعْنُ، لَزه لَزاً. والزِّرْفِيْنُ، وكذلك اللزَازُ. والتَزَائزُ: جَمْص، لَزِيْزَةٍ؛ وهي مُجْتَمَعُ اللحْمِ فَوْقَ الزَّوْرِ. والتَلَزْلُزُ: التَحَرُّكُ، ما تَلَزْلَزَ من مَكَانِهِ.</div>"}]}}